<tr>
<td><b><a href="/wiki/Dragon_dance" title="Dragon dance">Dragon dance</a></b> and <b><a href="/wiki/Lion_dance" title="Lion dance">Lion dance</a></b></td>
<td>Dragon and lion dances are common during Chinese New Year. It is believed that the loud beats of the drum and the deafening sounds of the cymbals together with the face of the dragon or lion dancing aggressively can evict bad or evil spirits. Lion dances are also popular for opening of businesses in <a href="/wiki/Hong_Kong" title="Hong Kong">Hong Kong</a>.</td>
